09 May 2019 06:04






I grew up in an area with quite a few water towers, and every time I would drive past them, I would always feel the strange urge to, if not climb them, then at least go near and potentially touch them; there was an odd sense of nostalgia and longing I'd associate with them, probably due to the fact that I'd see them almost every day but never actually interact with them. So as weird as it might sound to say, I'm glad that someone's finally made a water tower-based SCP, and that it turned out as good as this one. I will admit that the bit at the end with Dr. Winters almost lost me, as it initially felt like an unnecessary hook tacked onto an idea that was already solid enough to stand on its own, but the bizarreness of the final addendum was able to convince me otherwise. Enthusiastic +1.








And if the whole world is crashing down fall through space out of mind with me.




